<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="289" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="10.[1864,3497,2001,3631]" pageId="10" pageNumber="289">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1866,2337,3387,3426]" pageId="10" pageNumber="289">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
<collectingRegion box="[2348,2422,3387,3426]" country="Cameroon" name="North" pageId="10" pageNumber="289">Not</collectingRegion>
assessed on 
<emphasis box="[2658,2989,3387,3426]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="289">The IUCNRed List.</emphasis>
There are only two known specimens of the 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:885887A2FFC58A23F89EFB79F66CD74C:052E606FFFC58A23F757F2CEF53BD4F5" box="[2203,2750,3439,3478]" name="Mount Mabu Horseshoe Bat" pageId="10" pageNumber="289" stateProvince="North">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[2203,2334,3439,3478]" pageId="10" pageNumber="289">Mount</emphasis>
Mabu Horseshoe 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[2684,2750,3439,3478]" pageId="10" pageNumber="289">Bat</emphasis>
</location>
, indicating it is difficult to find. Its distribution is presumably small, but it could be larger. Additional sampling is needed to clarify its conservation status.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
